news.headline: Job Openings Increase Slightly In August, Higher Than Expected
news.summary: Job openings increased slightly in August, hitting 7.227 million vacancies according to the latest Job Openings and Labor Turnover Survey (JOLTS)

news.headline: Labor Market In New Era Of Low Churn, Uneasy Calm, Government Job Losses, And Crackdown On Illegal Immigration
news.summary: The red-hot turnover in the labor market has settled down from the chaos and churn in 2021 and 2022.

news.headline: Buy High Visibility Cash Flows For The Rate Cut Cycle

news.headline: September Charts: Stocks Defy Seasonal Weakness, Tech Led The Charge
